<section id="sec-title-slide"><h2>FYO-00205 Lecture 01-01:</h2><br><h1>Dimensions, Units and Conversions</h1>
</section>

<section>
<section id="slide-orgb6da688">
<h2 id="orgb6da688">0.0: Preliminaries</h2>
<ul>
<li>0.1 If you want to follow along with your own mobile device</li>

</ul>
<p target="_blank">
<a href="https://zak71.github.io/reveal.js/Lect_0_19-20_1-02.html" target="_blank">https://zak71.github.io/reveal.js/FYO-00205/2020-21/Lect-01-01.html</a>
</p>

</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org5076c78">
<h2 id="org5076c78">1.0: Quantities</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org5076c78">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-org9306060">
<h3 id="org9306060">1.1: Dimensions</h3>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
All quantities in mechanics are composed of three base quantities refered to as dimensions.
</p>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">length, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right]\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">time, \(\left[ \rm{T} \right]\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">mass, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right]\)</li>

</ul>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
when discussing electricity and magnetism we also include
</p>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">charge, \(\left[ \rm{Q} \right]\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgdb2364c">
<h3 id="orgdb2364c">1.2: Combinations</h3>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
Combinations of these base quantities make up other quantities
</p>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">speed, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-1}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">acceleration, \(\left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">speed, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right] \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">kinetic energy, \(\left[ \rm{M} \right] \left[ \rm{L} \right]^2 \left[ \rm{T} \right]^{-2}\)</li>

</ul>
</section>
</section>
<section>
<section id="slide-org2b0836e">
<h2 id="org2b0836e">2.0: Units</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org2b0836e">
</div>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgbaee59f">
<h3 id="orgbaee59f">2.1: Types/sizes</h3>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
Units are essentially dimensions that are given a measure
</p>
<p class="fragment (roll-in)" style="text-align:left">
These come in different sizes
</p>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">length: 
<ul>
<li>metre \(\left(\rm{m}\right)\)</li>
<li>foot \(\left(\rm{ft}\right)\)</li>
<li>mile \(\left(\rm{mi}\right)\)</li>
<li>furlong \(\left(\rm{fur}\right)\)</li>
<li>fathom \(\left(\rm{ftm}\right)\)</li>
<li>lightyear \(\left(\rm{ly}\right)\)</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgbaee59f-split">

<h3>2.1: Types/sizes</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">time: 
<ul>
<li>second \(\left(\rm{s}\right)\)</li>
<li>day \(\left(\rm{d}\right)\)</li>
<li>year \(\left(\rm{yr}\right)\)</li>
<li>svedberg \(\left(\rm{S}\right)\)</li>
<li>jiffy</li>
<li>lustrum</li>
<li>millenium \(\left(\rm{M}\right)\)</li>
<li>megannum</li>
<li>aeon \(\left(\rm{AE}\right)\)</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-orgbaee59f-split">

<h3>2.1: Types/sizes</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">mass: 
<ul>
<li>kilogram \(\left(\rm{kg}\right)\)</li>
<li>tonne \(\left(\rm{t}\right)\)</li>
<li>slug \(\left(\rm{sl}\right)\)</li>
<li>pound \(\left(\rm{lb}\right)\)</li>
<li>atomic mass unit \(\left(\rm{u}\right)\)</li>
<li>electronvolt \(\left(\rm{eV}\right)\)</li>
<li>solar mass \(\left(\rm{M_{\odot}}\right)\)</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
<section id="slide-org090b038">
<h3 id="org090b038">2.2 SI units</h3>
<ul style="text-align:left">
<li class="fragment roll-in">International system of units (Système international d'unités)</li>
<li class="fragment roll-in">base system known as metre-kilogram-second (MKS)  
<ul>
<li>length, metre \(\left(\rm{m}\right)\)</li>
<li>time, second \(\left(\rm{s}\right)\)</li>
<li>mass, kilogram \(\left(\rm{kg}\right)\)</li>

</ul></li>

</ul>
</section>
